,"format-standard","hentry","category-scholars-ulema","tag-anger-al-ghadab","tag-bad-deeds-al-sayyiat","tag-enmity-al-adawah","tag-forbearance-al-hilm","tag-forgiveness-al-maghfirah","tag-friendship-al-saddaqah","tag-good-deeds-hasanat","tag-manners-adab","tag-pardon-al-afwa","tag-patience-sabr","tag-satan-shaytan","tag-surah-fussilat","tag-wrongdoing-al-thulm"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-9HR","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":26137,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/03\/27\/ahnaf-manliness-hilm\/","url_meta":{"origin":37315,"position":0},"title":"Ahnaf on Manhood: True men are forbearing, forgiving","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 27, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Mada\u2019ini reported: It was said to Al-Ahnaf ibn Qays, may Allah have mercy on him, \u201cWhat is manhood?\u201d Al-Ahnaf said, \u201cForbearance at a time of anger, and forgiveness at a time of power.\u201d Source:\u00a0al-Muru\u0304'ah 64 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u0650\u064a\u0644\u064e \u0644\u0650\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0646\u064e\u0641\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0633\u064d \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0631\u064f\u0648\u0621\u064e\u0629\u064f \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u0650\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f \u0639\u0650\u0646\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u063a\u064e\u0636\u064e\u0628\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2810,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/06\/shaytan-anger-seek-refuge\/","url_meta":{"origin":37315,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Anger: Seek refuge from Satan inciting rage","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 6, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Sulayman ibn Surad reported: Two people insulted each other in the presence of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and the eyes of one of them became red like embers and the veins of his neck were bulging. The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, I know a word\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2761,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/03\/anger-satan-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":37315,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Anger: If you are mad, perform ablution with water","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"'Atiyyah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace be and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, anger comes from Satan, and Satan was created from fire. Fire is extinguished with water, so if you become angry, perform ablution with water.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4784 Grade:\u00a0Hasan (fair) according to Ibn Hajar\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24723,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/04\/24\/control-anger-defeat-satan\/","url_meta":{"origin":37315,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Rage: Strong man controls anger, defeats Satan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 24, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, passed by people wrestling, and he said, \u201cWhat is this?\u201d They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, this is a wrestler, and no one can wrestle like him!\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cShall I not tell you who is even\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34743,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/21\/real-strength-control-anger\/","url_meta":{"origin":37315,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Anger: Real strength is one who can control his anger","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 21, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhom do you consider to be a fighter among you?\u201d We said, \u201cOne whom men cannot wrestle down.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cIt is not so. Rather, it is one who controls himself when angry.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":38103,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/08\/13\/shaytan-plays-ball\/","url_meta":{"origin":37315,"position":5},"title":"Wahb on Iblees: Satan plays with anger like a child with a ball","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 13, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Mundhir reported: Wahb ibn Munabbih, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cSatan, upon whom is the curse of Allah, said: Verily, we lie in wait among the people of impatience and fury, then we play with them as children play with a ball.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd li-Ah\u0323mad ibn H\u0323anbal 522\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37315","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=37315"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37315\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=37315"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=37315"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=37315"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}